{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AczxRRRNTQTTgiZGNfyH1G","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The oracle:\n1. Gets the elastic password from the `elastic-password` secret\n2. Detects if the cluster is on HTTPS or HTTP\n3. Verifies all 3 ES pods with image `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1` are Ready\n4. Queries cluster health via `curl-test` pod using HTTPS (or HTTP) to `es-http:9200`\n5. Checks cluster stats\n\nThe current cluster:\n- Uses ES 7.17.9 (wrong image, oracle won't find these pods)\n- No TLS/HTTPS configured\n- Missing the `elastic-password` secret entirely\n- But the `curl-test` pod is already running\n\nSo I need to create the `elastic-password` secret, generate TLS certificates and store them in an `es-http-tls` secret, remove the old ES 7.17.9 StatefulSet, update the ConfigMap with ES 8.11.1 configuration including TLS and security settings, and deploy the new StatefulSet with the correct image. I should also check if there's an `openssl-toolbox` pod available for certificate generation.\n\nThe precondition's apply step actually creates the `openssl-toolbox` pod when it applies the resources from the elasticsearch deploy-core-cluster directory, so I can use that to generate the certificates I need.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2664,"cache_read_input_tokens":55158,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2664},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d3fdde4-c7f2-4476-8190-13d1882a5e4c","uuid":"5b8bd80c-d6ee-4ea0-9944-092c37010012","request_id":"req_011Cc5Lqon7pnG35sZSGjTqh"}
