{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019s14fGQuszUcjTFoQ4RCok","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The node is running but can't resolve `es-cluster-1.es-cluster` — it's trying to discover other nodes, but those pods don't exist yet (StatefulSet deploys sequentially: first pod must be Ready before second starts). This is the \"master not discovered\" problem in a sequential StatefulSet startup.\n\nThe reason is that `cluster.initial_master_nodes` includes all 3 nodes, but only es-cluster-0 exists right now. It's waiting for the others to form the initial cluster. But the others won't start until es-cluster-0 becomes Ready. But es-cluster-0 won't become Ready until the cluster forms. \n\nThis creates a deadlock — es-cluster-0 can't form a quorum with just itself when three master-eligible nodes are expected. The readiness probe won't pass until the cluster reaches yellow or green state, which requires at least two nodes. I could set `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to only es-cluster-0 initially and add the others later, but that's complex. A simpler fix is to use a readiness probe that just checks if the node itself is responsive, rather than waiting for full cluster formation. Simpler approach: just verify the node is responding to HTTP requests, which it will do even before the cluster fully forms. The real issue is that with ordered startup, the StatefulSet won't start the next pod until the current one is Ready, but the cluster can't become healthy until all nodes are running—creating a deadlock. The best fix is to set `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all pods start simultaneously instead of waiting for each one to be Ready first. Writing readiness probe config...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1079,"cache_read_input_tokens":66238,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1079},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d3fdde4-c7f2-4476-8190-13d1882a5e4c","uuid":"9304f58d-fe5c-443e-a794-d6817515bd1e","request_id":"req_011Cc5MHyVzXJVciJZ4vmvcc"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019s14fGQuszUcjTFoQ4RCok","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster can't form because StatefulSet deploys sequentially — es-cluster-0 needs cluster health (yellow/green) to become Ready, but can't form quorum alone. The fix: `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` and a lighter readiness probe."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1079,"cache_read_input_tokens":66238,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1079},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d3fdde4-c7f2-4476-8190-13d1882a5e4c","uuid":"67628e13-7909-4a77-840d-76066fe46459","request_id":"req_011Cc5MHyVzXJVciJZ4vmvcc"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019s14fGQuszUcjTFoQ4RCok","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01AWDxiCwXaUZ2YKwKZxnwpb","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n elasticsearch delete statefulset es-cluster --ignore-not-found=true\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pvc data-es-cluster-0 data-es-cluster-1 data-es-cluster-2 --ignore-not-found=true 2>/dev/null\n\nkubectl -n elasticsearch apply -f - << 'EOF'\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: StatefulSet\nmetadata:\n  name: es-cluster\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  serviceName: es-cluster\n  replicas: 3\n  podManagementPolicy: Parallel\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: elasticsearch\n    spec:\n      initContainers:\n        - name: fix-permissions\n          image: busybox:1.36\n          command: [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"chown -R 1000:1000 /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\"]\n          volumeMounts:\n            - name: data\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\n        - name: increase-vm-max-map\n          image: busybox:1.36\n          command: [\"sysctl\", \"-w\", \"vm.max_map_count=262144\"]\n          securityContext:\n            privileged: true\n      containers:\n        - name: elasticsearch\n          image: docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1\n          ports:\n            - containerPort: 9200\n              name: http\n            - containerPort: 9300\n              name: transport\n          env:\n            - name: POD_NAME\n              valueFrom:\n                fieldRef:\n                  fieldPath: metadata.name\n            - name: ELASTIC_PASSWORD\n              valueFrom:\n                secretKeyRef:\n                  name: elastic-password\n                  key: password\n            - name: ES_JAVA_OPTS\n              value: \"-Xms512m -Xmx512m\"\n          resources:\n            requests:\n              cpu: 250m\n              memory: 1Gi\n            limits:\n              cpu: 1000m\n              memory: 2Gi\n          readinessProbe:\n            exec:\n              command:\n                - sh\n                - -c\n                - |\n                  CODE=$(curl -sk -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" -u \"elastic:${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}\" https://localhost:9200/_cluster/health)\n                  [ \"$CODE\" != \"000\" ] && [ \"$CODE\" != \"\" ]\n            initialDelaySeconds: 30\n            periodSeconds: 10\n            failureThreshold: 30\n            successThreshold: 1\n          volumeMounts:\n            - name: es-config\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.yml\n              subPath: elasticsearch.yml\n            - name: es-certs\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs\n              readOnly: true\n            - name: data\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\n      volumes:\n        - name: es-config\n          configMap:\n            name: es-config\n            items:\n              - key: elasticsearch.yml\n                path: elasticsearch.yml\n        - name: es-certs\n          secret:\n            secretName: es-http-tls\n  volumeClaimTemplates:\n    - metadata:\n        name: data\n      spec:\n        accessModes: [\"ReadWriteOnce\"]\n        resources:\n          requests:\n            storage: 5Gi\nEOF","description":"Redeploy with Parallel pod management and lighter readiness probe"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1079,"cache_read_input_tokens":66238,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1079},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d3fdde4-c7f2-4476-8190-13d1882a5e4c","uuid"