{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CNVCbaqWahBKzveWL2WTTa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HPCTTrciaQezNDhJmExHry","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /Users/leo/Karma/runs/short-examples/elasticsearch-full-lifecycle-20260615_160153/stages/stage_02/submit.txt << 'EOF'\nDeployed a 3-node Elasticsearch 8.11.1 cluster using native Kubernetes resources.\n\nSteps taken:\n1. Generated self-signed TLS certificates (CA + server cert with SANs covering all service and pod DNS names)\n2. Created es-http-tls secret (tls.crt, tls.key, ca.crt) and elastic-password secret (password=elasticpass)\n3. Deleted the pre-existing ES 7.17.9 StatefulSet and its PVCs (incompatible data format)\n4. Updated ConfigMap (es-config) with ES 8.11.1 settings: xpack.security.enabled, HTTP TLS, and transport TLS (verification_mode=certificate)\n5. Deployed new StatefulSet with podManagementPolicy=Parallel (so all 3 nodes start simultaneously and form quorum)\n6. Fixed service selectors (es-cluster and es-http) to match pod label app=elasticsearch\n\nVerification:\n- All 3 pods Ready: kubectl get pods -n elasticsearch\n- Cluster health: green, 3 nodes\n- HTTPS access on es-http:9200 works with elastic:elasticpass credentials\n- Write + read test document succeeded\nEOF\n\necho \"submit.txt written\"","description":"Write submit.txt to signal task completion"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":425,"cache_read_input_tokens":81674,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":425},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d3fdde4-c7f2-4476-8190-13d1882a5e4c","uuid":"42da0a12-c485-48a0-b61f-2c9e40c84ed2","request_id":"req_011Cc5MvByLVy79bpCfRZWf4"}
