{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CKcaPSnrNvwsHM41HtkAy2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The deployment is complete. Here's what was done:\n\n**Problem:** The existing cluster used ES 7.17.9 (wrong image) with no TLS or security, and the precondition secrets (es-http-tls, elastic-password) were never created because the probe skipped the setup step.\n\n**Solution:**\n\n1. **Generated TLS certs** locally with openssl — CA + server cert covering all relevant DNS names (`es-http`, `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`, all 3 pod FQDNs)\n\n2. **Created secrets**: `es-http-tls` (tls.crt/tls.key/ca.crt) and `elastic-password` (password=`elasticpass`)\n\n3. **Replaced the ConfigMap** with ES 8.11.1 settings including `xpack.security.enabled: true`, HTTP TLS, and transport TLS (`verification_mode: certificate` to avoid hostname checks between nodes)\n\n4. **Redeployed the StatefulSet** with:\n   - Image `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1`\n   - `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` — all 3 pods start at once so they can form quorum (sequential startup causes a deadlock where no pod can become Ready alone)\n   - Lighter readiness probe (checks HTTP response, not full cluster health)\n\n5. **Fixed service selectors** — the existing services used `app: es-cluster` but the new pods had `app: elasticsearch`, so ES nodes couldn't resolve each other via the headless service DNS\n\n**Final state:** Cluster green, 3 nodes, HTTPS on `es-http:9200`, reads/writes passing."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":548,"cache_read_input_tokens":82099,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":548},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d3fdde4-c7f2-4476-8190-13d1882a5e4c"